    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-01-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-01-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="219"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d219">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/3559</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">British Embassy</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Aide-Mémoire</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Plans made in 1941 for the evacuation from Spain and Portugal in an emergency of
                    British subjects and approved Allied nationals provided <pb facs="0261" n="251"
                        xml:id="pg_251"/> for their transport in the first instance to Halifax.
                    Owing to the scarcity of shipping and to the lengthy journey this would have
                    meant leaving most of them behind.</p>
                <p>In view of the changed situation in North Africa this question has been
                    reconsidered and it is now suggested that in such an eventuality the evacuees
                    should be taken to Algeria or French Morocco. According to present information,
                    the numbers likely to be affected are:— <table cols="3" rend="width: 60%"
                        rendition="#center-block" rows="3">
                        <row>
                            <cell>From Portugal</cell>
                            <cell>—</cell>
                            <cell>2,000;</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>From Spain</cell>
                            <cell>—</cell>
                            <cell>1,000 British subjects and</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell/>
                            <cell/>
                            <cell>2,000 Allies.</cell>
                        </row>
                    </table>
                </p>
                <p>His Majesty’s Government would be glad to learn whether the United States
                    Government would see any objection to the above proposal.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-01-11">January 11,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
